serif: Fall's actually a pretty busy season, with school functions, exams and even seasonal events.

The leaves of the Ginkgo trees have turned a beautiful yellow.
It's finally fall.
The weather's been getting more and more temperate. I wish it were always fall...
Classes, exams and shows! Fall's a busy season, but I like all these things so much, I'll just need to pace myself and do my best.
Rin said my maple leaf hair tie's really cute! Hehe. I'm so glad I bought it♪
What do I do?! The sweet potato desserts Hona made were so yummy, I ended up eating way too many!
While we were out on a walk, Shibao picked up a maple leaf with his mouth and brought it to me. It was such a happy surprise!
The temperature's been fluctuating quite a bit lately, so it's probably best to carry around an extra layer, like a cardigan.
One of my neighbors brought over a lot of sweet potatoes, so I tried making them into desserts. What do you think?

Something I've been into besides bass?
I guess I'd say calligraphy.
Fall's a nice season for the arts, huh...? Music also counts as an art, so I guess that means we're engaged artistically all year round.
I don't really prefer one season over another, but I guess fall might be one of the better ones since I don't end up sweaty.
People say saury is good in fall, but it's also the season for salmon!

Oww, I slipped on some leaves, and Haruka saw the whole thing...
Now my backside hurts and I'm embarrassed...

Do you think we could get a food commercial offer or something?
Everyone, salmon tastes great this time of year!
Or something like that!
Maple leaves... I once recorded a music video where I was dancing on a beautiful red carpet of them.
We're making confetti that looks like maple leaves with Miku and the others. It won't be easy since we have to make a lot, but I'm actually kind of looking forward to it.
When fall comes around, I always end up searching for any acorns that look like a penguin. It's kind of embarrassing how childish I can be.
Hehe. For idols, fall means singing and dancing! Come on, let's give it what we've got!
Miku and the others said they're gonna do a show while wearing kimono-themed costumes. They're gonna look so amazing with all the maple leaf confetti they'll have showering down on them.
Minori keeps talking about which foods are in season lately, but... She knows that won't be enough to get us a commercial offer, right?
I'm a little cold... Why won't Shii ever come snuggle up with me?
Oh, this fallen maple leaf looks so beautiful. I think I'll craft it into a bookmark.

The way the leaves change color and fall is quite atmospheric.
That being said, where am I?

Was that a cricket chirping?
In the middle of a busy town like this?
It's been getting chilly lately, so I need to keep a close eye on the temperature inside Count Pearl's cage.
Peach buns are delicious this time of year. Hehe, I think I'll ask my mom to go buy some.
Miku said she's gonna roast some sweet potatoes... But that's not hard, so she'll be fine...right?
If we're gonna sing outside, I prefer when it's cool. Singing always makes us work up a sweat!
Hey, Kohane! There's a stand here selling roasted sweet potatoes! They look great, so let's buy some!

The air's been getting drier.
It might be good to warm up a little longer today to keep from hurting our voices.

Chestnut cheesecake, huh?
Ena's probably gonna get on my case if I buy just one...
Huh, so this type of outerwear is in this year...? Not my usual style, but might as well try putting something together.
Akito seems to enjoy the fall weather. Unfortunately, he gets frustrated thinking people are calling his name when they're actually saying "fall" in Japanese.

Seeing some fall foliage?
Would everyone be willing to come along if I invited them to join me?

A lot of bookstores have put up book recommendations.
Most of them have been great reads. I'm glad they haven't steered me wrong.
You know, I used to play Donguri Korokoro on the piano about as much as Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star.

Ah, if it isn't Nene! Are you here to see this troupe's production as well...?
W-Wait, where are you going?!
Fall means art! Art means shows! And where there's shows, there's Tenma Tsukasa, future star!
I love the rustly, crinkly sound of leaves crunching under my feet when I walk!

I went shopping with Rin☆
Here, look! I got a mushroom hat that goes over your entire head!
Hey, everyone! The Otori Group has its own farm, so how about we go pick some grapes or pears?

I came to see this troupe I like do a performance, but that obnoxious voice... It has to be...
I'll just pretend I didn't hear anything.
Rui said he gave Robo-Nene another new function... Huh? How? She can shoot maple leaves out now?!
Times of year when you can live without A/C sure are nice. It does wonders for my sleep too.
Fall's such a wonderful time to read. Unfortunately, the library doesn't carry much of the technical literature I've been looking for...

Thank you for the help, Len.
The device we just made should explode... I mean, make for a wonderfully artistic show.
The weather's finally cooled down a bit. Now I shouldn't have to worry about Robo-Nene undergoing thermal runaway.
I think the red maple leaves and rows of Ginkgo trees are very beautiful, but I wonder how Mafuyu feels about them.
An exhibition for fall scenery...? It could give me the inspiration I need to compose more songs.
I stepped out for a walk and found this Ginkgo leaf that's such a pretty color. I guess it's that time of year already.
The arts...? Are there works out there that can help me feel things like when I listen to Kanade's songs...?
Fall's the season for reading...? I think I'll bring Miku another picture book. Len might also enjoy it...
Fall's all about food...? Well, I guess I don't mind watching Kanade and the others eat...
What is it with people who look at a drawing or painting and go, "That's so artistic"? At least say it's "beautiful" or "amazing", you know?

The rows of Ginkgo trees would make for a great photo. As for the composition...
Okay, I'll take it from over there.
Huh? There's still half of this lip gloss left. Ugh... I went and bought a new one because I thought I was out.
The new fall/winter collection at the store I work at is totes adorable!

There are lots of opinions out there, but I say fall is the season of... Cuteness!
But then again, which season isn't♪
Whoa, my fingers got all dry... Where'd I put that hand cream?
The weather is much more pleasant now that it's a bit cooler!

How do you all like to spend fall?
With the arts, delicious food, or something else?
When the seasons change, it really makes you want to do seasonal activities.

Oh, look at the maple leaves! They're such a pretty color.
I wonder if I could get a costume like that.
I kinda wanna try making a bonfire from fallen leaves. Then we could all roast sweet potatoes and stuff in it♪
It sorta feels like there's less time to have fun when the days get shorter, but there are some things you can only do at night!
Why do chestnuts and sea urchins look so similar when one's from the land and the other's from the sea? What a mystery.

It's fall, so let's get out and exercise!
KAITO, we should play some sports together!
Rin and I were talking about finding fun stuff you can only do at night. Staying up late is always exciting.

It's getting cooler out, but the temperature still jumps up now and then.
It's hard to choose what to wear.
Instead of singing myself, it might be nice to spend some time listening to an orchestra this fall.
The sea breeze in summer is nice, but the crisp wind of fall is so refreshing and pleasant.
How does listening to some jazz on a quiet autumn evening sound? I'd be more than happy to sing if you need some vocals.
Fall could also be considered a season for choirs since so many competitions take place this time of year. Maybe I should try forming a choir too.
From food to the arts, there are a lot of ways to enjoy fall. Better plan things out so you can get to everything you want to do!
Luka and I were just saying how the bright red maple leaves remind us of MEIKO!
Len invited me to play some sports with him... Something along the lines of badminton might be nice.
Rin and Len are talking about staying up late and coming up with all these plans. Maybe I'll join them.
Seems like there are all kinds of school events in fall. Hehe, I hope everyone makes lots of memories!

The weather has gotten cooler.
Make sure to keep an eye on your health when the seasons are changing like this.
Ichika and the girls brought over roasted sweet potatoes. They were so sweet and gooey, I couldn't believe it.

Haruka drew a penguin face on an acorn.
It looked quite cute!
Did you know that cosmos come in so many different colors and types? I honestly couldn't believe it when Haruka told me.
Look! This outfit has a maple leaf theme. It's really cute, so I want to wear it in a show soon♪
The air can get very dry from this time of year, and a sore throat's the enemy of all singers.
Since fall's such a great time for sports, we're going to have a dance competition in SEKAI. You're welcome to come watch us if you like.
When the seasons change, it makes you want to try something new. Maybe I'll see if I can find something...
Hey, KAITO! What's a "mackerel sky"? Is that when it rains a buncha fishies?

We wanna do a fall show too☆
Would it help if we covered the stage in maple leaves?

I've heard some people get sad this time of year. But it's okay☆
I'll make everybody smile♪

Now and again, I see Ena sketching something in SEKAI.
Is it because fall is good for art...?
Are Kanade and the others happy about nights being longer in fall?
Kanade brought me a Ginkgo leaf... It was cute and pretty...

Saki's always fully decked out in the winter.
She keeps herself warm with hats, scarves, gloves, and even thermal underwear.
The weather has started getting quite dry lately. I better take care of my skin so I don't get any cuts when I play my guitar.

The news was saying this might be a warm winter...
But it's still pretty cold, huh?

We're having a hotpot party this weekend♪
I can't wait to eat Hona's cooking!
TA-DA! I brought enough heat packs for everybody today! Here, one for you, and one for you♪

I don't do great with cold weather, but I still want it to snow...
I mean, who doesn't wanna play in the snow?!
The winter night sky is so clear and beautiful that even though it's cold, I end up going outside to look for the stars.
Eep, the water is so cold! It's always painful to make rice during this season... You really need to rinse the grains with water before cooking them.

Warm miso soup and such taste even better in the winter.
Hehe, I just had some this morning.

I don't care if it's cold.
Don't cling to me, Shizuku!

Oh, this part might be good for getting warmed up before practice.
I have to move my fingers a lot for it, which should help with the cold.
Pumpkins taste best starting in fall, and they really are delicious. I eat them quite a bit boiled or as tempura.

Keeping everyone's hearts warm!
I'm Minori Hanasato, and I'm aiming to be the kotatsu of the idol world!
Huh? No good?
Samo is so full of energy during winter! He runs full speed ahead during our walks, so I always have trouble keeping up.

A...Achoo!!!
Ah! I-It's not what you think! I'm taking deep breaths, not sneezing!

Oh, there's a zoo where you can see penguins walking on snow.
I'd like to go visit someday.
Tis the season to have hot pot, huh? It might be fun to have another hot pot party stream with everyone sometime.
Minori tells people she's "taking deep breaths" every time she sneezes, but...it's a bit of a stretch...

Step one, moisturizer! Step two, moisturizer!
Idols need to take care of their skin.
A hot pot party stream sounds good... We're not planning to make some mystery concoction and eat in the dark, are we?

I don't jump straight to assuming a cold just because someone sneezed, but...
It can't hurt to keep yourself warm.

I'm cold... Um, Shii...?
Wait, why are you walking away?
Let me snuggle up with you...!
I made myself miso soup with napa cabbage for a winter treat today. But it becomes a little difficult to drink if I put it in my thermos.
Minori seems to be taking extra care of her health so that she doesn't end up being unable to work.

Eek! *Sigh*
I get a shock every time I pick up the mic...
My cheeks and nose tend to get red quickly from the cold. Then everyone gets worried and asks if I'm okay.
This winter exclusive chocolate ice cream looks really good. I think I'll buy some as a pat on the back to myself.
Oh! There's someone singing outside in this cold weather... I'm not gonna lose to that!
Wow, the wind is so cold. Does Haruka still run every morning even in this kind of weather? I definitely couldn't.
KAITO! Kohane found this really good chocolate ice cream. Do you want to have some with us?
Ugh. On top of this cold weather, why did it have to rain today? I better message everyone to meet up in SEKAI for practice instead.
Is it just me or does the whipped cream on pancakes and stuff taste sweeter when the weather gets colder?

Hot chocolate is great this time of year.
What, am I not allowed to drink hot chocolate?
I only came into this arcade to get out of the cold, but... That fluffy plushie looks really warm...
I know why and how our breath turns white, but it really is interesting to see.
Hot chocolate? It'd be nice to have some to warm myself up, but the way it's usually prepared is a bit... No, definitely too sweet for me.
Hah hah hah hah! Since I always make sure to take care of my skin, I am invincible to things like dryness!
A snowman onesie? Well, if it's for a show I don't mind... How do you put this on, though?
Playing in the snow... Well, if that is Saki's wish! I'll just use some styrofoam like Emu did once upon a time...!

Grr... It's still not snowing!
Oh, I guess I can just make my own snow☆
Nene! Nene! If the snow builds up, let's definitely make a snow hut together☆

Watch me, Nene!
*Inhale* BWAAAAAAH!
See?! I sounded like a monster, right?

Robo-Nene gets so cold this time of year.
It's almost too cold to touch...
A snow hut? I don't think it will snow enough to make one, but if it does, I want to try making one too.

Emu suddenly shows up at Kamiyama High, and what does she do...
Uh huh, you sounded like a monster, alright.
Lights appear a lot brighter since the air is clearer during winter. I might use more lighting effects for our next show.
Snowmen are one of the most popular winter-themed characters. So, Tsukasa, would you mind becoming one for me?

Tsukasa, you're covered head to toe in white specks.
They appear to be styrofoam, but what's the reason for that?
A humidifier? Can't I just use the steam that comes from my kettle whenever I make instant noodles?
This video's snow and ice effects are so amazing... How did they do that? Maybe Mizuki would know.

Winter's a pain. If I don't dry my hair properly, I'll catch a cold.
I can get away with cutting corners in the summer...
People hate the winter because of the cold, but I don't really mind it. I wonder if my name has anything to do with it.
Shouldn't you be more worried about eating too many sweets as opposed to wearing too many layers, Ena?

The steam from a kettle will humidify a room.
But it's in the kitchen, so you won't be able to humidify your room with it, Kanade.
I'm getting lots of good selfies since festive illuminations make for a great background.
Winter clothes are cute, but you immediately become a ball of clothes as soon as you start layering. It's so hard to have a balance...

This time of year always makes me want to eat really rich chocolate desserts.
Maybe I'll invite Mizuki and the others along.

*Yawn*
It's cold today, so I'm just gonna stay cozy in bed.
Whoa! This video Kanade just showed me is incredible! The effects are insane, but the rendering of the snow and ice is on a whole new level.
You see a lot more warm and fluffy clothes in winter, so even the silhouette of an outfit ends up looking cute!
It's interesting how snow is so fluffy and shiny even though it's cold.
Winter songs tend to be more on the romantic side. It makes me want to sing softer than usual.
They say winter air is nice and clear. Does that mean my singing will ring out farther than usual?

Everyone's songs ring out so clearly in this winter air!
Hey, "ring" sounds like my name!
Hey, Len! Let's visualize ourselves going skiing and snowboarding! So all you gotta do is go SWISH SWOOSH SHOOP like this!

Scoop, and throw! Scoop, and throw!
Hehe, I'm visualizing what I'll do in a snowball fight for the next time we get enough snow!

Lovely scarf, KAITO!
Hehe, mind if I borrow this end?
Snowboarding and other winter sports are so cool! I wonder if I'd be able to do them with practice.
Wait, Rin's visualizing what to do in a snowball fight? No fair! I've gotta practice too while I have the chance!
Oh my, Len and Rin are twisting their bodies into interesting poses... Are they practicing a new dance?
I heard that there's fireworks during winter too. How lovely, I'm sure they'd look beautiful with the air so clear.

It's even harder to get out of bed on winter mornings.
Take care that you don't end up running late.
When it's cold, take it easy and keep warm!
Snowboarding is great and all, but I've always thought ski jumping is so cool! I would love to try it at least once♪
The cold is tough to handle, but cool, clear air always wakes you right up.
The days are short in winter, but that means you can spend more time looking at the clear night sky.
Playing in the snow... Sports are fun, but I'd also enjoy making a snow hut and relaxing there.

I like winter quite a bit.
After all, ice cream tastes great this time of year.
The seasons are changing, so I'd better put extra care into doing maintenance on my guitar!
Leo/need's sound is so crisp and clear, like the winter air... We should work on our sound to achieve something like that.

Oh... Hehe, Saki, your nose is red.
You should get warm before we start practice.
Singing on stage while it's snowing would be so dreamy!
——♪ Alright! Let's do our best during today's show to deliver everyone cheer and smiles in this cold winter weather!
I want to dance in warm outfits and caps since it's winter, but... It gets really hot...
I know that practicing in the winter is tough, but your hard work will show in your music. I hope you can keep it up.
Since Vivid Bad SQUAD have been practicing so hard despite this cold weather, Rin and the others have been pulling out all the stops too. Hehe, I like where this is going.

A snowball fight sounds interesting.
If only it would snow in SEKAI, we could all have a battle.
KAITO, what do I need to do to make it snow?
Getting all cozy under a kotatsu and eating mandarins with everybody sounds so fun☆ We should get warm and munch on snacks too!
If we make Old Man Winter smile with our shows, will the spring come faster?
Is it cold where you all are, Mafuyu? I'd like to see the snow with Rin and the others sometime...
Len seems worried about Kanade and the others catching a cold. I think they'll be okay.
SEKAI doesn't have winter... But I still want to wear the things everyone brought over. Is it because they're so warm?
Happy birthday, Shizuku. We'll all be watching your birthday livestream today!
Hehehe, it was so fun making a cake with everyone♪ I wonder how Shizuku will react!
I got here early to give Shizuku her present, but... There's already such a long line in front of the classroom.

Happy birthday, Shizuku.
No, I'm not going to walk to school with you just because it's your birthday...

Happy birthday, Shizuku!
Let's celebrate a whooole lot during the birthday livestream!

Wow, we've gotten so many messages wishing Shizuku a happy birthday...
It even makes me happy.
I picked out some gifts that'll help with relaxation. Get rid of that fatigue so we can keep doing our best tomorrow!
The segment we're doing for today's stream is something I requested. Everyone's done so much to prepare for it... I can't wait.
I also got some pictures of everyone making the cake, so I want to give those to Shizuku the next time I get a chance.

Happy birthday, Shizuku!
Let me and Kohane sing for you when you're free!
So it's Hinomori's birthday? I'm still surprised somebody as amazing as her is willing to hang out with Ena...

So today is Shizuku's birthday. Thinking back, we've known each other for quite a long time.
I shall celebrate to the fullest!
Hehe, I played a role in Hinomori's birthday celebration, thanks in part to Mizuki's invitation.
Happy birthday, Hinomori. I'm sure you're busy with work... But feel free to drop by the archery club whenever you like.

I just know the limited edition color from this makeup brand will look great on Shizuku.
I'm glad I was able to get it.
Alrighty! Got the present all ready♪ Is Shizuku gonna like our surprise?
Everyone here in SEKAI is putting up a whooole lot of decorations for Shizuku's birthday party♪
I was afraid Santa would stop coming by this year, so I'm glad he made it.
My nose gets red right away in the cold, but it's cute how I'm like that red-nosed reindeer, right?
It's Christmas, so I'd like to prepare a heartwarming meal for Ms. Yoisaki and Asahina.
I put my present in Shizuku's room last night, but I'm sure she'll figure out it's from me.

Merry Christmas, Samo!
Here's a yummy dog chew for— Wah!
N-Not yet! Sit!
I'm looking forward to our gift exchange stream. I'd be happy getting a gift from any of them, but getting my own gift would be okay too.
Haruka said she'd be okay with getting her own gift in our gift exchange... So, she definitely brought something penguin-related.
I didn't think I'd be getting a present from Shii, too! I have to go give her mine!
We're having a party in SEKAI after practice today. Hehe, I can't wait to have some of MEIKO's cake.

The shop's closed, so Mom and Dad are going to enjoy the holiday with just the two of them!
It's a good opportunity, so take it easy!

Oh right, I'm supposed to pick up that cheesecake we ordered.
Gotta head over there before I go to SEKAI.

I never imagined I'd celebrate Christmas twice in one day, once with family and once with friends.
This should be a fun day.

Saki. Priding yourself on your red nose is perfectly fine, but you need to wear your scarf properly!
As for your coat, maybe something a bit thicker—

When I woke up, my present to Santa was gone!
I'm so glad he accepted it♪
I'm having a Christmas party with Emu and the others, but I wonder if they'll like the gift I brought for the exchange...

Ah, yes. Maybe I ought to deck Robo-Nene out in Christmas colors?
No telling Nene, of course. Hehehe.

Oh, um... Merry Christmas.
Hehe. It feels weird exchanging this sort of greeting at home.
Mochizuki made us some stew, but it's a bit different from the stew my mom makes...
Ugh, when is Akito going to bring the cheesecake home? Hurry up already.

Sis sent a postcard!
Whoa, it looks like everyone's excited for Christmas over there too.

Have you all been nice?
Today, us Santas will give you the wonderful gift of song♪

Merry Christmas! It's fun to celebrate back-to-back since my anniversary is close by!
I hope you all have fun too!
Did everybody get their gifts from Santa? Hehe, I got mine!

How are you all spending the day?
Hehe. I'd like to hear about it, if you don't mind!

Merry Christmas! Do you have all your presents and treats ready?
I sure do!
We'll have to do plenty of decorating to really get into the Christmas spirit.

We tried using the decorations Ichika and the others brought to deck the classroom out.
Now all that's left is to have our party.
Christmas means exchanging gifts♪ It's always exciting wondering who brought which package, and what's inside!
Kohane and the others are going to have one party in SEKAI and another at home. I'm jealous they get to have two celebrations.
Ho ho ho! I'm Santa. Where are the good boys and girls? I've got presents for all of you!
We're also going to celebrate in SEKAI... Do you think KAITO and MEIKO will come...?

Happy anniversary, Rin.
Oh...? You have some whipped cream on the corner of your mouth.

Happy anniversary, Rin♪
There's some whipped cream left over from when we were making your cake, so do you wanna eat it together?
We got together with Rin and the others to all make an anniversary cake from scratch. Hehe, it's got lots of fruit and whipped cream.

Saki, Rin, what are you eating?
What? I don't need any.
I'm not becoming an accomplice.

Happy anniversary, Rin!
Wait, you're in the middle of a meet and greet-slash-autograph session?!
Wh-Where do I line up?!

Are preparations for your show coming along, Rin?
You're not sure what accessories to use...?
Okay, I'll help you decide.
Minori, it's not fair that you're the only one who got an autograph! Here, take my post! I'm going to line up.

Rin's meet and greet-slash-autograph session, right this way!
Oh, MEIKO, you're lining up as well? Of course, go ahead.

Happy anniversary, Rin!
We're working with Len to get your gift together, so look forward to it!

Rin and Len are going to give each other presents.
They're so close! That's what it means to be partners!

Whichever of them surprises the other with their gift is the winner...?
Can't those two just celebrate normally?

Happy anniversary, Rin.
Sorry to say, but I'm on Len's team.
I can't give you any hints about your present.

Today is Rin's anniversary!
I'll need to take this moment to do some vocal exercises so that I can celebrate it thoroughly!
Here it is, me and Rui's "Operation: Which Do You Want, the Right Or the Left? Just Kidding, Take Both!"♪

Happy anniversary, Rin.
Huh, Tsukasa's yelling really loud?
Oh, you don't have to worry about that.

Why, Rin, you look pleased.
Emu surprised you...?
I see. That's wonderful!

Happy anniversary, Rin.
How was the cake Ena and Mizuki picked out for you?

Happy anniversary, Rin.
That cake is from a store at the station, so I'll bring more sometime.
Happy anniversary, Rin. We thought really hard about what cake to get, so I think you'll be happy with it.

Happy anniversary, Rin♪
Well, how do you like the cake and the new ribbon that came with it? Cute, right?

Happy anniversary, Rin!
Let's do lots to celebrate♪

Everyone!
It's my anniversary today♪
You've gotta come celebrate with me, you've gotta!

Happy anniversary, Rin!
Let's both have lots of fun as the stars of the day!
Happy anniversary, Rin. I found this lovely flower. Would you like to try putting it in your hair?

Umm, so everything is ready for the party, all that's left is...
Oh, did we have party poppers somewhere?

Happy anniversary, Rin.
Hehe, no need to get ready all in a rush, the day isn't going to run off anywhere.
Saki and Rin were putting away the leftover whipped cream and fruit, so I had some as well.

Happy anniversary, Rin!
I'm looking forward to your show! Also, I want an autograph too♪

Happy anniversary, Rin.
Hopefully, the gift An and the others helped you come up with surprises Len.

Happy anniversary, Rin♪ I hear Rui and Emu put together a surprise for you?
Hehe, that's great☆

Happy anniversary, Rin...
Um... Oh, do you want to eat this strawberry that was on the cake?
It looks like Saki and Rin are sneaking mouthfuls of whipped cream, so I should call Len over too.

Happy anniversary, Len♪ We were just putting away the leftover whipped cream...
Th-There's nothing sneaky about it!

Oh, Len. There's some fruit left over from when we were making your cake.
Please take some, if you'd like.

Happy anniversary, Len. Oh, you got roped into becoming their snacking accomplice?
Well, you're one of the stars of the day, so I figure that's fine.

Happy anniversary! Wait, Len, you're having a meet and greet-slash-autograph session too?!
Woohoo, I'll get right in line!
Happy anniversary, Len. Oh, a meet and greet-slash-autograph session...? You don't see that every day, so I think I'll get lined up.
Oh, Shizuku! I'll take over guide duty, so why don't you go to Len's meet and greet-slash-autograph session?

Happy anniversary, Len.
This is a little something from Rin to help you replenish your energy.
She says, "Let's do our best during the show".
Len, I brought over what you asked for. I hope it makes Rin happy.
Happy anniversary, Len! Oh, nonono! I'm on Rin's team, so I can't tell you anything!

Happy anniversary, Len. Oh, what I'm carrying...? Dunno, what do you think?
Anyway, look forward to it.
Len and Rin both seem to be having fun getting their gifts ready. I hope they're able to surprise each other.

Today is Len's anniversary!
I'll need to start the day off right with some warm-up exercises so I can celebrate to the fullest!
Look, Len, look! Tsukasa's racing around! Let's join in♪
Emu and Rui are going to surprise Rin, and Tsukasa and I are going to surprise Len, but... Where did Tsukasa go?

Happy anniversary, Len.
And Tsukasa, Nene is waiting for you, so I'd appreciate it if you could go talk to her.

Happy anniversary, Len.
How was shopping? I hope you enjoyed it.

Happy anniversary, Len. Were you just singing a song from the CD we bought with Mizuki and the others...?
Yeah... It's a nice one.
Happy anniversary, Len. Is there anything you want to do? It's fine if you act selfish today.

Happy anniversary, Len!
It's a special occasion, so how about getting prettied up?
I'll bring some clothes that should look good on you!

Happy anniversary, Len♪
Hehe, everything's ready for the party, so look forward to it.

Happy anniversary, Len!
Luka gave me this flower. Do you wanna try putting it in your hair too?
